# Docusaurus Documentation Card Pattern

## IMPORTANT: Use UI Components Library

**BEFORE creating any card-based UI in Docusaurus, ALWAYS check the UI components library first:**

1. **Location**: `ui-components/` folder (outside `docusaurus/` folder)
2. **Import Path**: `@ui-components` (configured via webpack alias)
3. **Available Components**: 
   - `CategoryCardGrid` - For displaying multiple cards in a grid
   - `CategoryCard` - Individual card component

## Card Structure for Category/Section Pages

When creating category index pages or section pages that display multiple subsections as cards, **ALWAYS use the UI components** from `@ui-components`:

```markdown
import { CategoryCardGrid } from '@ui-components';

# Category Name

Category description.

<CategoryCardGrid
  cards={[
    {
      title: 'Subsection 1',
      description: 'Description of subsection 1',
      href: '/docs/section/subsection1',
    },
    {
      title: 'Subsection 2',
      description: 'Description of subsection 2',
      href: '/docs/section/subsection2',
    },
  ]}
/>
```

## Rules:

1. **ALWAYS use UI components**: Never write raw HTML for cards. Always import and use `CategoryCardGrid` from `@ui-components`
2. **Check component library first**: Before creating any new card-based UI, check `ui-components/src/` to see if a component already exists
3. **Component location**: UI components are in `ui-components/` folder (outside `docusaurus/` folder) at the repository root
4. **Relative paths**: Use relative paths from the component location when importing dependencies within the UI components library
5. **Consistency**: Using the UI components ensures consistent styling and behavior across all pages

## Fallback (Only if UI component doesn't exist):

If you need a card pattern that doesn't exist in the UI components library:

1. **First**: Create the component in `ui-components/src/` following the existing pattern
2. **Then**: Use it in your MDX file

The raw HTML pattern (for reference only - prefer components):
- `<section class="row list">` - outer container
- `<article class="col col--6 margin-bottom--lg">` - card wrapper
- `<a class="card padding--lg cardContainer" href="...">` - card link
- `<h2 class="text--truncate cardTitle">üìÑÔ∏è<!-- --> <!-- -->Title</h2>` - card title with icon
- `<p class="text--truncate cardDescription">Description</p>` - card description

